Best concise meeting summary

This is probably the strongest concise framing:

The current implementation maintains runtime counters in the database to enforce exact supplier sequencing. Under high concurrency, this creates contention because all requests update shared rows. A stateless weighted-routing approach removes runtime database writes entirely and provides statistically accurate distribution over volume while significantly improving scalability and operational stability.

If someone pushes back on randomness

Your response:

Modern distributed systems and load balancers commonly use weighted probabilistic routing because it scales much better than maintaining synchronized counters across concurrent requests.

That is technically true and sounds credible without being combative.

